fields.Title: WHIRLING F1 ORB / dialogue karaoke inspiration
fields.Placement: In front of the stage of the downstairs whirling. (this pops up when you've clicked all three orbs on the stage) But only IN FRONT, where you can assess the stage. ON the stage there's another orb

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "You should sing the sad, slow song..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You should sing the sad, slow song you were listening to last night. Thought it was obvious...

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "Who is mistakenly identified as a c..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Who is mistakenly identified as a cop for his prominent jaw line? Yes, sounds likely. You should probably go on stage and pose for a moment when you're done with this thought. See if it works.

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "You should sing the sad small churc..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You should sing the sad small church song from that tape you found. Thought it was obvious...

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "You have not yet stumbled on the ri..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You have not yet stumbled on the right *lamentation*. But it's out there. It'll come to you. You'll wreak havoc with it, don't worry.

fields.Title: You: "Lamentation sounds good. They'll re..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Lamentation sounds good. They'll really get a gauge on my soul with that.

fields.Title: Half Light: "Whether they like it or not. Ram it..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Whether they like it or not. Ram it up their ears, says your adrenaline gland. Violently express yourself.

fields.Title: You: "I was thinking maybe I could sing s..."
fields.Dialogue Text: I was thinking maybe I could sing something happy. Get the people going.

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "You have to find out how the song g..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You have to find out how the song goes first, though... maybe a tape of something appropriate would help.
fields.Alternate1: You would need another copy of the tape first, though. The one upstairs is destroyed.

fields.Title: You: "My soul is immense."
fields.Dialogue Text: My soul is immense.

fields.Title: You: "[Discard thought.]"
fields.Dialogue Text: [Discard thought.]

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "Utterly. And it needs to be heard."
fields.Dialogue Text: Utterly. And it needs to be heard.

fields.Title: You: "My soul is puny."
fields.Dialogue Text: My soul is puny.

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "Exactly. It's measured, level-heade..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Exactly. It's measured, level-headed, and it needs to be heard.

fields.Title: You: "[Finish thought.]"
fields.Dialogue Text: [Finish thought.]

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "There has been precisely no evidenc..."
fields.Dialogue Text: There has been precisely no evidence to the contrary. So yes, Yes, it's likely. You should probably go on stage and pose for a moment when you're done with this thought. See if it works.

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "You should sing the sad, small chur..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You should sing the sad, small church song, duh. Thought it was obvious...

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "Serves them right! Wipe that smirk..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Serves them right! Wipe that smirk off their face with your sad, tragic song. Who's laughing now? No one.

fields.Dialogue Text: You have to find something tragic to sing first, though.

fields.Title: You: "What should I sing, when it comes t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: What should I sing, when it comes to it?

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "You should totally sing karaoke her..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You should totally sing karaoke here, the first chance you get. Your emotions need to be expressed. People need to know of your vast, oceanic soul.

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "By other people."
fields.Dialogue Text: By other people.

fields.Title: You: "I was thinking maybe I could sing s..."
fields.Dialogue Text: I was thinking maybe I could sing something happy. Get the crowd going.

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "Of course. Like a small animal that..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Of course. Like a small animal that only comes out at night. All it needs -- is to be heard.

fields.Title: You: "I was thinking maybe I could sing s..."
fields.Dialogue Text: I was thinking maybe I could sing something happy. Like, from those Ostentatious Orchestrations folks...

fields.Title: You: "Of course! They'll really get a gau..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Of course! They'll really get a gauge on my soul with that one.

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "Serves them right! Wipe that smirk..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Serves them right! Wipe that smirk off their face with your sad, tragic song. Who's laughing now? No one.

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "Of course. At this point, precise m..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Of course. At this point, precise measurements of your soul can only be performed from the outside. It needs to be heard.

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "You should sing that sad song you w..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You should sing that sad song you were listening to last night. Thought it was obvious...

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "Through a PA system."
fields.Dialogue Text: Through a PA system.

fields.Dialogue Text: No-no, don't sing the happy song, it's stupid. Sing the sad song, it's profound.

fields.Dialogue Text: No-no, don't sing the happy song, it's stupid. Sing the sad song, it's profound.

fields.Dialogue Text: My soul is modest. It's normal sized.

fields.Dialogue Text: My soul's cubic content is obscured by the hangover.

fields.Title: You: "This goes well with a theory I'm de..."
fields.Dialogue Text: This goes well with a theory I'm developing: that I'm a down-on-my-luck superstar person.
